{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611840","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611840"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:18:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:18:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16251"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16251","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16251"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.04,0.04,0.86,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8942"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66704"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8942","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8942"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16251"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52157"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9872"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21277"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21281"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66704","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66704"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cardiovascular system undergoes several physiological changes as part of the normal aging process.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following cardiovascular parameters increases with normal aging?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Maximum heart rate capacity","Beta-adrenergic receptor sensitivity","Ventricular compliance","Peripheral vascular resistance","Baroreceptor sensitivity"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWith aging, \u003Cstrong\u003Eperipheral vascular resistance\u003C/strong\u003E increases due to arterial stiffening, reduced nitric oxide production, and endothelial dysfunction. This contributes to the rise in systolic blood pressure commonly seen in older adults.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaximum heart rate capacity\u003C/strong\u003E decreases with age and can be approximated using the following formula: 220bpm - age in years\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBeta-adrenergic receptor sensitivity\u003C/strong\u003E decreases with age, resulting in reduced responsiveness to both endogenous and exogenous catecholamines\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVentricular compliance\u003C/strong\u003E decreases with age due to increased myocardial stiffness and fibrosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBaroreceptor sensitivity\u003C/strong\u003E decreases with age, leading to increased blood pressure variability\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese age-related changes in the cardiovascular system contribute to increased risk of hypertension and other cardiovascular diseases in older adults.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Peripheral vascular resistance increases with age due to arterial stiffening and endothelial dysfunction.","Aging reduces cardiovascular responsiveness to catecholamines and decreases ventricular compliance.","Maximum heart rate decreases with age according to the formula 220 minus age in years."],"references":["Maier JA, Andr\u00e9s V, Castiglioni S, Giudici A, Lau ES, Nemcsik J, Seta F, Zaninotto P, Catalano M, Hamburg NM. Aging and Vascular Disease: A Multidisciplinary Overview. J Clin Med. 2023 Aug 25;12(17):5512. doi: 10.3390/jcm12175512. PMID: 37685580; PMCID: PMC10488447.","Jani B, Rajkumar C. Ageing and vascular ageing. Postgrad Med J. 2006 Jun;82(968):357-62. doi: 10.1136/pgmj.2005.036053. PMID: 16754702; PMCID: PMC2563742.","Seals DR, Jablonski KL, Donato AJ. Aging and vascular endothelial function in humans. Clin Sci (Lond). 2011 May;120(9):357-75. doi: 10.1042/CS20100476. PMID: 21244363; PMCID: PMC3482987.","Seals DR, Jablonski KL, Donato AJ. Aging and vascular endothelial function in humans. Clin Sci (Lond). 2011 May;120(9):357-75. doi: 10.1042/CS20100476. PMID: 21244363; PMCID: PMC3482987."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52157"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16251"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52157","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52157"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T19:50:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T19:51:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8942"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66704"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Re